<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="terms-n">terms <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /tɜːmz/    美 /tɜːrmz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[复数] 条文；条款；表达方式：</strong></h4>
<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-terms-of">in terms of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>从…方面来讲；就…而言：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In terms of size and population, how big is the European Union compared with China?
与中国相比，欧盟的面积和人口规模如何？</p><footer>外研③ – 2</footer></div>

<h3 id="be-on-good-terms-with">be on good terms with</h3>
<p>1.<strong>与…关系好：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We were on good terms with everyone in the village.
我们与村子里的每个人都相处得很好。</p><footer>外研⑥ – 3</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong><em>_</em></strong>_ achievement, last week's ministerial meeting of the WTO here earned a low, though not failing, grade.  （2006 湖南）<br />
A.In terms of<br />
B.In case of<br />
C.As a result of<br />
D.In face of  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. A  </p></div>